# SECRET_SCAN_ALLOWLIST
# Paths excluded from the CHECK 9 secret scan in validate.sh.
# One path prefix per line. Lines starting with # are comments.
#
# Rules:
# - Each entry MUST have a justification comment on the immediately preceding line
#   Format: # owner: @handle — reason: <why this path is safe>
# - Use the narrowest possible path (specific file, not a directory)
# - Wildcard entries (docs/, *.md) are rejected by the governance check
# - New fixtures/examples touching flagged patterns must be added here with justification
# - Allowlist changes must be reviewed in PR like any other code

# owner: @ensell-yes — reason: docs example showing what a secret scan failure looks like; no real credentials
CONTRIBUTING.md
# owner: @pipeline — reason: contains literal scan pattern strings used in grep calls
scripts/validate.sh
# owner: @pipeline — reason: this file is the allowlist itself; entries are path strings not credentials
